I have returned from Arizona...it was good. Kinda rainy, but we got some sun too, it was really warm on Sunday. It was my GREAT Grandfathers 100th birthday, so thats why i was down there. I got to meet everyone (almost) on my dads side of the family, which was completly awesome. It was a fun expierence, and it made Pa (great grandfather)really really happy to see all of us together for him. It made me wanna cry, it just meant so much to him to meet his 9 great grandchildren adn see his grandchildren for the first time, in some cases, for 20 years. It was really great.
           


I got a sweet shirt while i was down there that says : Born To FCUK (french connection united kingdom) hehe...looks like fuck doesnt it?

Alright so brace yourself for this...the single most bizzarre christmas eve ever, and thus leading to a bizzarre christmas i suppose.

  so 6am xmas eve morning i wake up and puke, and continue to puke and dry heave every half hour after that until 11am. My grandma and mom then both take me to this weird clinic (my normal doctor was gone), and all the people in this clinic, i swear, were from the twilight zone...they were all nuts. So about 30 minutes of waiting in a doctors room, a big man with tatoos on his arms comes in to give me a shot ::shutters at the thought::. Not 10 minutes after the shot, i pass out, not go to sleep, PASS OUT...out like a fat kid in dodge ball. I was out for a while, so i dont really remember anything that happened in that time. Except that i think i had an out of body experience cuz according to my mom there were no mirrors in the room, however i remember looking myself in the face. I also remember wondering if i was dying. So first i got all white and waxing looking, and heard a "fizzing" noise in my ears, and a ringing noise too, then i turned all rosey, and got all sweaty, then i got all white again. Also my mom said i was making weird groaning noises. And apperantly i kept slipping out of my wheelchair too while they were trying to get me into our car. 

   Once home from the "crazy clinic" i stayed in my "passed out" state and slept for hours and hours and was woken few times to drink a little bit of water. Then i slept till this morning, woke up tp open presents, went back to bed, and woke up again at 3.

merry christmas

its too easy for others to meet you there.
so perk up and see the light,

cuz you'll be sorry for the waste of time

come to understand
that tomorrow brings a new day.

hhmmmmm ::in most whiney tones possible::

  So today my car got sick and decided to puke up coolint all over the ground. Thankfully just as she blew i had just parked. Every last bit of green liquid coolint was out of her in a jiffy. SO sat Jenica on the curb outside of the Olympian Newspaper building, awaiting Sarah and some guidence. Thankfully she called up Plum Street auto, and grandpa Shelstad came to the rescue with more coolint and advice for me to eat up. Grandpa Shelstad insisted we bring bessie back to the shop for a check up. So my mother, grandpa, and sarah and I made a nice little train down to the auto shop. On the way down there my poor little car got sick again and started steaming, thankfully she didnt puke again until we parked at the shop. And thats where she is now. Again, i am carless (for the time being anyway). One taste of freedom, one day to do what i need to without depending on others...and BAM! its gone. thats it. thats all i get.



...figures.


much love to you, and you, and yes, even you!

All guys are the same. Thats what I have come to. Not in every aspect of course, but when it comes to planning they definatly are. I'm all for being spontanous; for spontanously dropping by and hanging out--not for spontanously saying you cant hang out. Or being so spontanous with other people that they cant make plans with me until 30 minutes before which usually follows with an "I cant" or "I'm not sure yet". I'm sick of it, but not like theres anything to do about it, right? Thats just the way they are, and I can either put up with it, or get rid of them and I dont want to do that. I dont want to be frustrated all the time either though. I'll take frustration for now I guess.

    Aside from guy trouble...I need a car really badly. I hate money, hate it, hate it, hate it!! It holds me back from a vehicle. Damn it. I'm frustrated all over the place tonite, and to make it worse, I worked all day today and have nothing to do tonite, on a saturday. fuck that man. this blows.

fuck money.

fuck cars.

fuck boys who cant plan.

 

sorry for my negitive attitude.

 

love to all who care.

So i have a meeting to attend to this morning at 7:30....yuk. SO now i am up! up up up up up! I dont think i have updated in a while though so here whats been goin on. First and foremost the PLP is suffering as one of our closest is away in Hawaii and wont return until the 27 and left about a week ago. On a jollier note, however, I WENT TO WARP TOUR! WOOT WOOT! It was kick-ass! We spent the night up at the gorge too, and just camped out there along with about one thousand other people. It was like one big party all night! Bouncing Souls, Flogging Molly, and Story Of The Year rocked it the most I thought, but this is also coming from someone who missed the first two hours ::sheds a tear:: which included many of the bands we actually went to Warp Tour to see. If I thought you cared that much, i would tell you what bands we missed but I'm sure you dont, so i will refrain.The fourth of July was awesome too! A whole bunch of us went out to my boyfriends house and we just lit off explosives and had a good time, my madre actually let me spend the night out there too. Kinda funny though cuz we had the shittiest fireworks out of everyone else on the lake haha.
